The paper focuses on the physical layer security performance of a mmWave cellular network, which involves the study of communication channels, network topology, and security measures. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves the use of stochastic geometry, which is a common tool in the analysis of wireless networks, suggesting the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The study of network-wide security performance falls under the category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of mmWave channels, which have unique characteristics compared to conventional microwave channels, suggests the category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of various network parameters, which falls under the category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
